### ============================================================
###  ROLE-BASED ACCESS TESTER
###  Anubhav Trainings | CAP | JWT Auth | Role-Based @restrict
### ============================================================
###  How to use:
###    1. Run the "ADMIN — login" request → copy `access` token
###       from response into the @adminJwt variable below.
###    2. Run the "USER — login" request → copy `access` token
###       into the @userJwt variable below.
###    3. Fire the catalog / user-management calls.
### ============================================================

### ── VARIABLES ──────────────────────────────────────────────
@base       = http://localhost:4004/odata/v4
@catalog    = {{base}}/catalog
@usermgmt   = {{base}}/user-management
@auth       = {{base}}/auth

### Paste the tokens you receive from the two login calls here
@adminJwt   = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhZTU5YTY4YS1kZDIxLTQ1MmYtOTlhMy1kYTgzODJmMTg0MGUiLCJyb2xlcyI6WyJBRE1JTiJdLCJpYXQiOjE3Nzg3Mzc1MjksImV4cCI6MTc3ODczODQyOSwiYXVkIjoiYWNjZXNzIn0.5s9BDGgehyzTBjyU9JvBAyl_FuUE4YSpTqC34LDe8Fg
@userJwt    = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJjNWM1YzVjNS0wMDA2LTQ1NTUtODU1NS01NTU1NTU1NTU1MDYiLCJyb2xlcyI6WyJUUkFWRUxMRVIiXSwiaWF0IjoxNzc4NzM3NjUwLCJleHAiOjE3Nzg3Mzg1NTAsImF1ZCI6ImFjY2VzcyJ9.Ggd6RwGZEv4u4oAv5L7vFgLOGc-DynaswNhlFaStU2A

### A traveller-role user that already exists in seed data
@userLogin  = raj.sharma@example.com

### ============================================================
###  PART 1 — ADMIN FLOW
### ============================================================

### 1.1  ADMIN — login (default admin created by user-init)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{auth}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loginName": "anubhav@anubhavtrainings.com",
  "password":  "Welcome1!"
}

###

### 1.2  ADMIN — who am I (verifies JWT + ADMIN role)
GET {{auth}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}

###

### 1.3  ADMIN — read ALL Travellers (admin sees every row)
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 1.4  ADMIN — read ALL TravelledLocations (admin sees every row)
GET {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations?$expand=traveller($select=firstName,lastName,userID)
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 1.5  ADMIN — read Destinations (admin can read & write)
GET {{catalog}}/Destinations
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###


### ============================================================
###  PART 2 — TRAVELLER (regular user) FLOW
### ============================================================

### 2.1  USER — login (a TRAVELLER-role user from seed data)
# @name userLogin
POST {{auth}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loginName": "raj.sharma@example.com",
  "password":  "Welcome1!"
}

###

### 2.2  USER — who am I (verifies JWT + TRAVELLER role)
GET {{auth}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{userJwt}}

###

### 2.3  USER — read Travellers (only own row visible)
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers
Authorization: Bearer {{userJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2.4  USER — read TravelledLocations (only own trips visible)
GET {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Authorization: Bearer {{userJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2.5  USER — read Destinations (allowed for any authenticated user)
GET {{catalog}}/Destinations
Authorization: Bearer {{userJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2.6  USER — anonymous call to Travellers → expect 401
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers
Accept: application/json

###

### 2.7  USER — Traveller hitting user-management → expect 403
GET {{usermgmt}}/Users
Authorization: Bearer {{userJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###


### ============================================================
###  PART 3 — ADMIN HITS USER-MANAGEMENT
### ============================================================

### 3.1  ADMIN — list Users
GET {{usermgmt}}/Users?$expand=roles($expand=role)
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 3.2  ADMIN — list Roles (code list)
GET {{usermgmt}}/Roles
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 3.3  ADMIN — createUser action
POST {{usermgmt}}/createUser
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName":  "Agent",
  "email":     "test.agent@anubhav.com",
  "roleId":    "AGENT"
}

###

### 3.4  ADMIN — assignRole action
POST {{usermgmt}}/assignRole
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "c5c5c5c5-0002-4555-8555-555555555502",
  "roleId": "ADMIN"
}

###

### 3.5  ADMIN — lockUser function
GET {{usermgmt}}/lockUser(userId='c5c5c5c5-0002-4555-8555-555555555502')
Authorization: Bearer {{adminJwt}}
Accept: application/json

###
